# Project structure

Human-readable mirror: [docs/01-overview/PROJECT_LAYOUT.md](../../docs/01-overview/PROJECT_LAYOUT.md) (keep in sync when layout changes).

- **Top-level layout**
  - `minecraftmod/` is the Gradle root for this mod (`settings.gradle` includes subprojects).
  - **`api`** — outward-facing Java API (interop surfaces); no Clojure game logic.
  - **`mcmod`** — platform-neutral foundation: protocols, DSLs, metadata, utilities (no Forge/Fabric or `net.minecraft.*`).
  - **`ac`** — platform-neutral game content and domain logic; depends on `mcmod` only (plus `api` where needed).
  - **`forge-1.20.1`** — Forge adapter: `@Mod`, registration, Java bridges, implements `mcmod` protocols.
  - **`fabric-1.20.1`** — optional Fabric adapter; may be omitted from root `settings.gradle` (default `include` commented).

- **mcmod (foundation)**
  - Clojure under `mcmod/src/main/clojure/cn/li/mcmod/...` with namespaces **`cn.li.mcmod.*`**.
  - Domain areas include: `block` (dsl, tile_dsl, tile_logic), `client` (obj, render), `events`, `gui` (api, cgui, container, core, dsl, network, …), `inventory`, `item` (dsl), `nbt` (dsl), `network`, `platform`, `registry`, `util`, etc.
  - No direct Forge/Fabric/Minecraft API imports; Clojure + data libs only.
  - No `src/main/resources` in this module (per `build.gradle`).

- **ac (game content)**
  - Clojure under `ac/src/main/clojure/cn/li/ac/...` with namespaces **`cn.li.ac.*`**.
  - Domains: `block`, `client/render`, `config`, `energy`, `gui`, `item`, `registry`, `wireless`, etc.
  - Depends on `mcmod`; uses mcmod DSLs/metadata; **must not** import Forge/Fabric/`net.minecraft.*`.
  - Shared assets: `ac/src/main/resources` (e.g. `assets/my_mod/`, `data/my_mod/`).

- **Platform modules (`forge-1.20.1`, optional `fabric-1.20.1`)**
  - `src/main/java` — loader entrypoints and Java-only glue.
  - Clojure adapters: `forge-1.20.1/src/main/clojure/cn/li/forge1201/...` → **`cn.li.forge1201.*`** (and similarly `cn.li.fabric1201.*` when Fabric is enabled).
  - Translate loader events into `mcmod` / lifecycle hooks; read metadata from `mcmod`/`ac` instead of hardcoding registry IDs.
  - Loader-specific resources: `mods.toml`, `fabric.mod.json`, loader-specific assets under each module’s `src/main/resources`.

- **Dependency red line**
  - **`ac` and `forge-1.20.1` must not reference each other** (no `cn.li.ac` requires from forge; no `cn.li.forge1201` from ac). Both depend on **`mcmod`** (and **`api`** where applicable).

- **Adding new content**
  - Extend DSL/metadata in **`mcmod`** when introducing new abstractions.
  - Implement gameplay in **`ac`** using `defblock` / `defitem` / etc.
  - Touch **`forge-1.20.1`** (or Fabric) only for loader-specific wiring; keep adapters thin.
